channel.title: Edgeville Gate Problem. [PROBLEM SOLVED]
channel.description:
Hello I'm having trouble deleting this object in my server [IMG]http://i57.tinypic.com/e0o0eo.png[/img] I put in the right coords because when I click the object it gave me the coords I am using a InsidiaXV8 base source. This is the code I'm using: c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(-1, 3079, 3501, 1, 10); not quite sure what is wrong with it but I really need someones help I've tried everything.
EDIT: I just realized that the pic said ladder instead of gate.

item.title: Edgeville Gate Problem. [PROBLEM SOLVED]
item.dc:creator: @1_2_3_4_KOED 1 2 3 4 KOED
item.description:
@1_2_3_4_KOED wrote:

Change the c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(-1, 3079, 3501, 1, 10); to
c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(-1, 3079, 3501, 0, 0);

item.description:

You may be trying to delete the wrong coordinates, try a few coordinates in your range.

ie if it looks like it’s in 10,10, try 9,9 10,9 etc. etc. Your client may allow you to right click it to get its absolute position too.
